&lt;li&gt;A Bachelor&#39;s degree in a technical field or Associates degree in a technical field and equivalent maintenance technician work experience.&amp;nbsp;Strong equivalent maintenance technician experience may be considered in lieu of educational requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automation and machine control experience with demonstrated troubleshooting

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Divergent is a technology company that has architected, invented, built, and commercialized an end-to-end factory system called the Divergent Adaptive Production System (DAPS) that comprehensively uses machine learning to optimally engineer, additively manufacture, and flexibly assemble complex integrated vehicle structures and subsystems. Products created using DAPS are superior in performance, lower in cost, rapidly customizable to meet mission and customer-specific requirements, faster to market, and scalable on demand to high volume production. Divergent is a qualified Tier 1 supplier to global automotive OEMs, and Divergent is now expanding to support mission critical needs in the Aerospace and Defense sector. Join us to be a part of this transformative journey, where your impact will shape the future of technology and production.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Purpose&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Automation Engineer supports the daily operations across all of our Robotic Work Centers, including Assembly, Part inspection, Anodize, &amp;amp; post processing lines, for Divergent’s flexible robotic manufacturing systems, core to the Divergent Adaptive Production System (DAPS). The ideal candidate will use their expertise in automated systems, industrial robotics, and off-line programming to maintain &amp;amp; generate robotic programs for production parts and ongoing internal projects, while working with cross-functional teams to capture and implement process improvement. Divergent is pushing the boundaries of technology and we need a passionate and agile engineer to help us create the platform for sustainable manufacturing.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Automation Engineer on the Advance Manufacturing team, you will be at the forefront of implementing advanced automation and robotics systems in our production environment. You will support the day-to-day operations; help refine processes and enable scalability. This role is hands-on, fast-paced, and essential to delivering high-precision, high-reliability hardware across automotive, aerospace, and defense programs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create Simulation Studies in Process Simulate on Teamcenter (Tecnomatix)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help create and maintain customer product manufacturing data for automated work centers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain kinematic libraries of hardware systems in robotic simulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate optimal assembly sequences and validate feasibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform reach &amp;amp; access studies and validate assembly sequence logic and interference-free robot motions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Program robots and automated systems to perform specific tasks and functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot and resolve any issues with existing automation systems to ensure smooth operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help create and maintain documentation for all automation and robotics systems, including specifications, manuals, and training materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Train and mentor other team members on the operation and maintenance of automation and robotics systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously monitor and analyze data from automation systems to identify areas for improvement and recommend solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide insight, data, &amp;amp; learnings to our development team to help inform our next generation robotic platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with suppliers and vendors to procure necessary equipment and components for automation projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to all safety protocols and regulations while working with automation and robotics systems&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Basic Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lawfully access information and technology that is subject to US export controls&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mechanical Engineering

